headline: J&J Seeks FDA Nod for Subcutaneous Tremfya as Induction Regimen in UC
summary: If approved, JNJ's Tremfya will be the first IL-23 inhibitor to offer a choice of subcutaneous or intravenous use as induction treatment in ulcerative colitis.
